					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/chatHub",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"chatHub"
							]
						},
						"description": "The endpoint for SignalR connection. In Postman, use 'New -> WebSocket Request' or a dedicated SignalR client."
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "### How to test SignalR in Postman:\n\n1.  **Open a WebSocket Request** (New -> WebSocket).\n2.  **URL**: `ws://{{base_url}}/chatHub` (or `wss://` if HTTPS).\n3.  **Methods**:\n    *   `JoinChat(string chatId)`: Call this to start receiving messages for a specific chat.\n    *   `SendMessage(SendMessageDto message)`: Use this to send a message.\n\n### SendMessage Body Example:\n```json\n{\n  \"chatId\": \"guid-here\",\n  \"content\": \"Hello World\",\n  \"senderId\": \"user-guid\",\n  \"senderType\": \"user\",\n  \"messageType\": \"text\"\n}\n```"
		}
